    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "What you are seeing is due to the fact that there is no call to display in your cell, and a display call is only being triggered at the end of the cell execution. \n\nWithout an explicit call to `IPython.display.display()`, what happens is equivalent to \n\n``` python\nplt.ioff()\nimg = np.random.random((10, 10))\nplt.imshow(img)\nimg *= 0\nplt.show()\n```\n\nIn which case you will see the same behavior you observe, even in the plain python shell. If you consider that behavior to be a bug, please report it to matplotlib.\n"
  },
